subSubSection.paragraph:
The molars decrease in dimensions from m1 to m3, the more so between m1 and m2 than between m2 and m3. Furthermore, from m1 to m3, the molars shorten, the molar trigonid becomes less dominant relative to the talonid (the ratio of trigonid length relative to total length decreases from m1 to m3; 
Table 1
), trigonid cuspids form a more and more closed triangle and tend to be less prominent and less well individualized from one another.
